tion of spells that allow them to solo fairly safely, without high end gear.  Of course in doing so you wont be as good a tank as a warrior, but that is the trade off for the ability to solo.  <p><FONT COLOR="green" FACE="forte" size="6point" >Myles Bonaduce</FONT> <P>

If I say a cow can lay an egg dont argue with me, just get the skillet!    Muhamed Ali</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ucuedyen2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuedyen2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00bie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 1:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: verant's pet class (rant)</span><hr size=1> Can't remember which board I was reading - but a warrior wrote a rant about how unfair it was that the hybrid classes are too powerful since they were balanced.<br>
<br>
The essence of his argument was that warriors were not as needed as before - people were actually taking paladins/sk as secondary tanks in grind groups over warriors.  What he failed to realize is this is balance - you will take one class over another.  You no longer need the &quot;holy trinity&quot; other classes can substitute.   In his mind it was better when you wanted 2 warriors, cleric, enchanter, and a rogue in a group and filled in the last position with anyone else.<br>
<br>
This sounds much the same.  In a grind group you will still want a couple of tanks (unless AE) but with class balancing other classes may be invited to play.  <br>
<br>
I don't know how many times I have been in an xp group needing another person and mages/druids/wizards/necro's pop up LFG and the party does not want them.  So now these classes are getting upgraded - good.  I hope that more balancing comes about.  <br>
<br>
And you will always have people who complain - no matter what VI does.   Everyone is entitled to an opinion but to say VI does not listen - how can they listen to everyone when everyone has a different opinion?  So if they (VI) disagree they don't understand balance and they don't listen.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ugoralondos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>goralondos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowls at you rdy to attack!</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 5:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=43>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: verant's pet class (rant)</span><hr size=1> I am the mage that Eldryc was talking about in the posts above so I wanted to contribute some comments to this post.  <br>
<br>
First, I soloed my way from level 1 to 60 becuase no one ever wanted to group with me, ever. As soon as I got my epic, I have found that people alway want me for groups when I could easily solo instead lol.<br>
<br>
Second, grouping with a 60 epic mage is different then what you are use to in a normal grind group.  Ussually in a normal grind group we have grown up on in Everquest, you will try for some kind of slower to minumize the damage being taken by the Tanks in the group, this is not as needed when you have a 60 mage in the group that can throw out a 33pt group DS for the tanks and a 50pt DS on an epic pet. Someone commented that grind mobs are a joke and I do agree completely with that statement.  For me there is no reason to bother slowing these mobs when you can have them destroy themselves on a nasty DS. <br>
<br>
I have watched the epic pet outdamage many combos of 60 melee like a warrior and rogue or 2 monks.  I do have a pretty good comparison in that I played a monk to 58 with epic before switching to a Mage. The Damage Per Second that a mage can product when needed is amazing.  I think Eldryc did a good job of fielding comments in this area because it is one of those things you have to see to believe. How I normally keep up with the fast pace pulling where the mage pet is alway taking one or more adds is I am lucky enough to have several Flowing Thoughts item, the 58 mana regen spell, and have many 60 chanter fiends to supply KEI. Also since my brother plays a 60 cleric, it is possible to use mod rods to fill our mana bars close to full if KEI is not availible. Of coarse having a 60 cleric healing the epic pet is also very helpful <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A lot has been said about how hard the mage epic is compared to other epics.  I have played Everquest for over 2 1/2 years now and made many friends on our server.  I found the mage epic to be easy with the help of friends.  <br>
I didn't start the epic until level 53 when one of my friends who farms hate found Magis up with the staff.  Once I got that piece, most of the rest fell into place in a couple days.  I MQed the Peggy Cloak, Undertoe, and CoM torch with RL friends and bought the phinny staff and sky crown.  The two I bought were very expensive, but I had a lot of money from alway soloing.  <br>
<br>
Finally, I would like to address some of the things people said about multiple mobs and mages taking hits.  I am at almost 1800hps with my Arch Shielding self buff. Since I picked an erudite I wear gear that gives me Hps and Mana where i can.  When I group with my brother (which is about 97% of the time) I will have aego which puts me over 3k hps.  So when I need to take a hit, i can.  <br>
When someone pulled more the one mob, I will do the following: if the mobs are seperated by poor pathing I will simply have the pet &quot;pick off&quot; the trailing mob.  If they are grouped tightly together I will try to find the one the Target the one the tank is not on and hit it with Scars of Sigil which is a very fast casting relatively low damage spell that will almost alway instantly peel the mob off the melee and on to me.  Once the mob has hit me or tried too the epic pet will get mad and attack. Epic pet almost alway leads in with a stun, whether it hits or not the mob is alway very mad at the epic pet and has completely forgot about me.  <br>
<br>
Overall, I would just say that mages are a wonderful class and if you get the chance grab a mage in your group and see what you have been missing.<br>
<br>
