<br>
In grind groups, the mage epic pet litterally kicks the shiit out of melee in time it takes to kill mobs.  We fought at toiler hill in ME one night with me (60 cleric), callon (60 War), Tiyra (59 Mage, at the time) and a 59 Monk w/epic.  Each person was basically single pulling and on average the mage pet was killing stuff about twice as fast as callon and the monk usually had his next mob at about 75% health by the time the one callon was on dropped.  Throw in the fact that I casted one Celetial elixer (1500 hp) on the pet for BOTH mobs and could either cast 2 or 3 on callon or 1 ce and a CH, thats just insane.<br>
<br>
Couple things plp might not know or just failed to realize.  In grind groups, Epic pets have a minimum hit of 22 damage and a max of 81.  Warriors minimum hit...... 1.  Now granted a warrior can crit for a lot more then that, but your talking about a pet that can hit no lower then 22 and seriously doesnt miss much compared to most melee (I have a ranger so I know how much melee miss).  Throw in that they can quad hit too, procs a 130 ish DD that goes off ever other minutes (the spam is sick if you dont turn it off) and a 80 point stun that lasts for 6 seconds.  Oh yeah, and that 50pt damage shield everytime the mob hits them, or 65 if I cast mark of retribution.  The fact alone that their minimum damgae is so high and they dont miss much explains so much why the pet just kicks the shiit out of stuff.  Another point, what happens if the pet dies?  Well if the mage is well prepared and has resummoned the epic at some point, a brand new ass kicking pet in 20 seconds.  Some people dont zone that fast after dying =P.  <br>
<br>
Should we care? To be perfectly honest, I am reaping the benefits b/c me and him can duo and get insane exp with little drain on my mana bar, hell I nuke once a battle most of the time.  The thing that sucks though is that in grind situations this pet can absolutly destroy mobs that other melee have trouble with.  I think Myles (hey buddy) brought up the point about the pets not being able to think, taunt or break mez etc...  I have seen numours times in group where my brother has broke a mez with a Scars of Sigil, had the mob agro on him and was able to step away seconds later after barely taking any damage.  The stun the pet procs is a uber taunt, things generally dont come off the pet once that stun lands.  When duoing I can chain cast CH on the pet with three mobs on it if I wanted to and get little if no agro b/c they dont have the coding in place for that from what I can tell.  Any other melee that has three mobs and after a remedy I'll be running around getting my ass kicked, let along a CH.  <br>
<br>
I think what finally blew Callon over the top was the fact that they improved the pets more recently.  The pet was kick ass before, its didnt need more power.  I have seen a group of mages do some sick shiit.  A little while ago, some of the mages on the server gathered together and camped epic stuff together.  I saw 6 mage pets taking out mobs left and right, if one died, SEND IN ANOTHER, WOOT!!!!!.   The mage epic is long,but to say it is the hardest is just wrong.  Sure it as a lot of little annoying shiit to camp, but what epic doesnt?  Throw in the fact that they can generally easily solo the mobs they need to camp minus the one hard part of each of the 4 orbs and its really not all that hard.  I mean hell, the crown from the POA is DROPPABLE, come on now.  Sure you need a decent amount of money to MQ a lot of the pieces, but like my brother said they can make a lot of money soloing stuff.  <br>
<br>
I leveled mostly by pick up groups till I hit about lvl 56.  I went back and thought about the number of times that I grouped with mages and couldnt think of very many.  I would venture to say that the number is probably around 10 times in 56 levels, I always remember my groups being cleric/enc + melee with the occasional druid thrown in.  I think being creatures of habit, most of us are not used to grouping with mages for really no good reason.  The point that mages suck in groups is utter BS because they can blast hard and the pets do nice damage even before the epic.  Granted, mages are generally a solo type class and most plp know that going into them, but anyone that wont take a mage in thier group when they needed damage is just dumb IMO especially if they have their epic.  I have more I could write, but I think that is way more then enough for now.  Off to go get some insane exp with my brother.........<br>
<br>
