actually that's not true in a grind group anymore, Elawnah.  Because of the AC softcap and several other reasons, other classes will tank just as well as a warrior.  Basically several classes are close enough to equal now in tanking ability that in a grind group it doesn't matter.  Go with the one that does the most damage (monk most likely) or one that supplies other utility that you need.  But that's a different discussion.  <br>
<br>
Here's the simplest scenario since it is in essence what my grind groups can get the majority of fights down to.  Yes, it's oversimplified, but it represents well what we go for on exp grinds and we can set up this type of 1 on 1 in most situations --<br>
<br>
Take a 60 warrior with decent gear, not uber guild stuff, just solid gear.  Hell, give him 200k for it.  I have 200k+ in gear and that's not counting much value for several pieces, including the bp and legs, which are no drop.  don't worry about how much the mage has in gear.  It doesn't matter.  They need an epic so assume much of their plat went toward buying MQ's or something.  The rest of it can be mediocre gear.  Figure, i don't know, 100k total for some mediocre gear and a bunch of MQ's to help get the epic.  anyway, that's too much detail for a simple test, so moving on...<br>
<br>
Now make an epic mage pet.  Use the water one.  It does great dmg.  Any of them will probably work though.  Throw on the buffs.  Assume you've got nice buffs (DS, haste, aego, etc. etc.).  Have a cleric ready to heal.  Bring in the average blue con grind group mob.  Bring one mob for the pet and one for the warrior.  If a mob dies, assume that it's very quickly replaced by another mob.  Now pay attention while they fight for a few minutes.  I guarantee you that the mage pet will kill it's mobs faster.  It's not close.  Okay, fine, I can deal with that if the old thought that pets are good dmg dealers but not good dmg takers applies.  It doesn't.  That warrior will require far more healing than the pet does.  I don't know entirely why that is.  The pet does have 30hp per tick extra regen, but that's only 300 per minute.  The warrior is going to be at the AC softcap for grind mobs.  But for whatever reason, but pet will not need near the healing that the warrior does.  That's the bottom line... better dmg but also better tanking.  Now how that's even a little balanced,  I have no idea.  If it does better damage, it should NOT take damage as well.  Period.<br>
<br>
-- Callon<br>
